        "title": "You've Been Shade-Matched Using an Outdated System",
        "body_text": "<p>Think about the last time you were shade-matched. Someone held a strip of colour against your jawline under fluorescent shop lighting, declared you a \"warm beige,\" and sent you home with a bottle that looked completely different by the time you got to your bathroom mirror.</p><p>This system is fundamentally broken. Your skin doesn't have one fixed shade. It shifts constantly — with the seasons, with your circulation, with the temperature, with the light you're standing in. A single static pigment will always look wrong somewhere, at some point during the day.</p><p>The breakthrough that women over 50 are discovering is tone-adapting pigment technology. Instead of matching a shade to one moment in one lighting condition, these intelligent pigments read your unique undertone and adjust in real time. The result is foundation that looks correct in every room, at every hour, without you ever second-guessing your shade choice again.</p>",
        "link_text": "",
